-- Regression for #285 (S0 silent wrongness): native Float `!=` on NaN was WRONG.
-- The specialized inline Float-comparison path emitted `fcmp <floatPred op>`, and
-- floatPred "!=" was "one" (ORDERED not-equal), which is false when either operand
-- is NaN -- so `nan != nan` printed False under `build` while `run` (eval) and the
-- wasm backend (f64.ne) gave the IEEE-correct True.  `!=` is the LONE relational
-- predicate that must be true for NaN, so it needs "une" (unordered-or-not-equal);
-- every other comparison is correctly ordered.  Fixed in floatPred
-- (compiler/backend/llvm_emit.mdk).  Pins run==build==value on the NaN `!=` edge and
-- the `==`/`<`/`>` NaN cases (all IEEE-false), plus non-NaN `!=` so the common case
-- and the `(a != b) == !(a == b)` identity are guarded too.
--
-- #288 (S0 silent wrongness, now FIXED): `<=`/`>=` on NaN.  eval derived them as
-- `not (ordGt/ordLt (valueCompare …))`, and wasm routed a two-global-operand compare
-- through the 3-way `$mdk_value_cmp` (-1/0/1) which cannot model NaN's unorderedness --
-- both wrongly printed True while native (inline `fcmp ole`/`oge`) gave the IEEE-correct
-- False.  Fixed: eval gained Float-specific IEEE arms (compiler/eval/eval.mdk), and wasm
-- now recognizes a top-level Float global so the compare lowers to inline `f64.le`/`f64.ge`
-- (compiler/backend/wasm_emit.mdk).  These four lines pin run==build==value on the NaN
-- `<=`/`>=` edge (all IEEE False) plus a NaN-vs-finite case.
--
-- #305 (S0 silent wrongness, now FIXED): the LAST NaN relational hole — a genuinely
-- POLY `Ord a` forwarded through a HOF, so the emitter cannot see Float statically and
-- routes to the runtime value-shape discriminator.  Native's mdk_value_cmp_raw and
-- wasm's $mdk_value_cmp are THREE-WAY (-1/0/1), a model that structurally cannot
-- express NaN's unorderedness: an unordered pair collapsed to 0 (EQ), and the caller's
-- `cmp <= 0` then read `nan <= nan` as True on BOTH backends while `run` (eval) said
-- False.  Fixed by giving the runtime PER-OP IEEE predicates (mdk_value_lt/le/gt/ge +
-- the $mdk_value_lt/le/gt/ge WAT peers) that answer a boxed-Float operand with a direct
-- f64 compare and use the 3-way only for the String/immediate shapes.
-- EMITTER-SEMANTICS §4 N5/N6: `<` `<=` `>` `>=` at Float are PRIMITIVE IEEE predicates
-- on EVERY path — never derived from `compare` — and all four are False at NaN.
--
-- The block below pins the DOMAIN, not just the headline repro (#476's lesson: a
-- differential gate only covers what it samples): all four ops x NaN on the left, the
-- right, and both, through the type-lost HOF — plus CONTROLS that must not regress
-- (ordinary Floats and Int both through the same HOF).

nan = 0.0 / 0.0

-- type-lost: `f` is opaque at the emit site, so the operands' Float-ness is invisible
-- and the comparison must fall to the runtime value-shape path.
applyCmp f x y = f x y
cmpLt a b = a < b
cmpLe a b = a <= b
cmpGt a b = a > b
cmpGe a b = a >= b

main =
  println (debug (nan != nan))   -- IEEE True  (the #285 bug: native gave False)
  println (debug (nan == nan))   -- IEEE False (ordered oeq, unchanged)
  println (debug (nan < 1.0))    -- False
  println (debug (nan > 1.0))    -- False
  println (debug (1.0 != 2.0))   -- True  (non-NaN != still works)
  println (debug (1.0 != 1.0))   -- False (non-NaN != still works)
  println (debug (nan <= nan))   -- IEEE False (#288: eval/wasm gave True)
  println (debug (nan >= nan))   -- IEEE False (#288: eval/wasm gave True)
  println (debug (nan <= 1.0))   -- IEEE False
  println (debug (1.0 >= nan))   -- IEEE False
  -- #305: all four ops through the type-lost HOF, NaN both sides — all IEEE False.
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLt nan nan))  -- False
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLe nan nan))  -- False (#305: native+wasm gave True)
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpGt nan nan))  -- False
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpGe nan nan))  -- False (#305: native+wasm gave True)
  -- #305: NaN on the LEFT only — all IEEE False.
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLt nan 1.0))  -- False
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLe nan 1.0))  -- False (#305: native+wasm gave True)
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpGt nan 1.0))  -- False
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpGe nan 1.0))  -- False
  -- #305: NaN on the RIGHT only — all IEEE False.
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLt 1.0 nan))  -- False
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLe 1.0 nan))  -- False (#305: native+wasm gave True)
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpGt 1.0 nan))  -- False
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpGe 1.0 nan))  -- False
  -- CONTROL: ordinary Floats through the SAME type-lost HOF must be unchanged.
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLt 1.0 2.0))  -- True
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLe 1.0 2.0))  -- True
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLe 2.0 1.0))  -- False
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpGt 2.0 1.0))  -- True
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpGe 1.0 1.0))  -- True
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLe 1.0 1.0))  -- True
  -- CONTROL: Int poly-Ord through the SAME HOF must be unchanged.
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLt 1 2))      -- True
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpLe 2 1))      -- False
  println (debug (applyCmp cmpGe 2 2))      -- True
